<div id="so_formfield_dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description_" class="field fld_description fld-ro">

            <div class="label" id="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description__field-label">
	<label for="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description_">Synopsis</label><span class="req-indicator"></span>:
      </div>
            
      	 	<div class="widget" id="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description__widget">
			<div class="notice_desc_dates">
				<span class="added">Added: <input type="hidden" name="dnf_class_values[procurement_notice][description][0][added_on]" value="2014-02-07 13:31:16">Feb 07, 2014 1:31 pm</span>
					</div>
		The US Environmental Protection Agency has a requirement for support services for the libraries/information facilities of the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) in Research Triangle Park   (RTP), North Carolina.  A cost type contract is contemplated but, offerors will be allowed to propose other contract types.<br /><br />
EPA maintains independent technical library/information facilities at RTP.  The EPA library contains approximately 2000 journals, 5,000 books, 13,000 paper documents, and 150,000 microfiche documents and provides service to a potential customer base of approximately 3,000 employees located in RTP and other EPA locations throughout the country.  In addition the library serves members of the public in their information needs.<br /><br />
Approximately 20,411 hours for the base year and 20,411 hours for subsequent option years are contemplated.  The library/information services to be provided range from the professional to the clerical and will be performed on-site.<br /><br />
Tasks include mail processing, serials acquisition and handling, circulation, acquisition support and classification, shelving and filing, reference assistance, interlibrary loan/photocopy, document release and referral services, records, procedures and reports, photocopy/duplication, travel to various conferences and library network meetings, web site support, marketing and outreach, collection development and library instruction program.<br /><br />
All materials and equipment necessary for performance will be furnished by the government.  The applicable NAICS code is 519120 with a size standard of $14 million in average annual revenue.  EPA has determined that the solicitation will be processed on a full and open competitive basis.  This requirement is follow-on to contract number EP-D-09-090 with the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.  <br /><br />
It is anticipated that the contract will have an effective date of 10/01/14.  The award will contain a 12 month base period of performance and four 12 month option periods.  RFP No. SOL-NC-14-00004 will be issued on or about March 10, 2014.  No further synopses will be issued.  Proposals will be due 30 calendar days after the RFP is issued.  Offerors will be evaluated based upon both technical and cost/price factors.  <br /><br />
Offerors must be able to provide personnel with education and/or experience in technical library information services.  The solicitation and any subsequent amendments will be available via the World Wide Web at http://www.epa.gov/oam/rtp_cmd/ only.<br /><br />
Hard copies or diskettes will not be available.  Telephone and Fax requests will not be honored.  It will be the offeror?s responsibility to frequently check the same site where the solicitation is posted for any amendments.


